textProperties.textString: Florence Nightingale's Crimean War Data Set
textAndAttributes: Florence Nightingale's Crimean War Data Set

textProperties.textString: Florence Nightingale introduced modern sanitation and care measures to military facilities in the Crimean War, drastically reducing the death rate among soldiers, and in particular the death rate due to  disease.  Her original graphic, showing the decline and death rate between her first and second years, is above; you can explore her data by adjusting the sliders  to change the range on the bar charts, to compare seperate intervals.  Clicking on a bar chart will show the detail for that month on the accompanying pie chart.
